      "content": "Minimum wage hikes are a significant financial pressure on small businesses, regardless of location. While the intention is to help workers, these increases directly raise operating costs, forcing owners to either absorb the losses or raise prices. In a rural area with lower existing consumer spending, this price increase can be a major threat to the viability of a small, local shop. Therefore, these laws often lead to reduced hiring or menu price adjustments, which is a serious risk for new entrepreneurs.",
